      "content": "interesting. when you mention the \"complex interplay of genetic, environmental, and socio-economic factors,\" which side of that debate is more supported by recent genomic research? Specifically, is there any evidence that these gaps are actually rooted in biological or hereditary differences rather than just social environment?",
